From: MIRA beta-readiness orchestrator (Lens A re-audit, 2026-06-08)
Subject: [PATCH] security(hub): tenant-scope cmms_equipment lookup in /api/documents

WHY: /api/documents resolves an asset's manufacturer/model via
`SELECT ... FROM cmms_equipment WHERE id = $1` on the raw RLS-bypass pool with NO
tenant filter. An authenticated tenant-A user (or the shared demo token) can pass
any asset UUID and read a tenant-B asset's manufacturer + model_number = a
cross-tenant IDOR. cmms_equipment is per-tenant OPERATIONAL data, not the
universal knowledge_entries corpus, so the #1761 precedent (/api/usage: keep
knowledge_entries untenanted, tenant-filter operational tables) applies directly.
Surgical: add `AND tenant_id = $2` to the one lookup; knowledge_entries query is
left as the documented universal corpus.

APPLY:
  cd <repo-root-MIRA>
  git checkout -b fix/documents-tenant-filter
  git apply wiki/orchestrator/patches/2026-06-08-documents-tenant-filter.patch

VERIFY:
  cd mira-hub && npx tsc --noEmit
  # request another tenant's asset_id => empty mfr/model (was: leaked); own asset => unchanged

diff --git a/mira-hub/src/app/api/documents/route.ts b/mira-hub/src/app/api/documents/route.ts
index a42b49bf..261e4023 100644
--- a/mira-hub/src/app/api/documents/route.ts
+++ b/mira-hub/src/app/api/documents/route.ts
@@ -36,8 +36,8 @@ export async function GET(req: Request) {
     if (assetId) {
       const asset = await pool
         .query(
-          `SELECT manufacturer, model_number FROM cmms_equipment WHERE id = $1 LIMIT 1`,
-          [assetId],
+          `SELECT manufacturer, model_number FROM cmms_equipment WHERE id = $1 AND tenant_id = $2 LIMIT 1`,
+          [assetId, ctx.tenantId],
         )
         .then((r: { rows: Record<string, unknown>[] }) => r.rows[0] ?? null);
       if (asset) {
